parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended acceleration of the vehicle can cause a loss of vehicle control, which can increase the risk of an accident, potentially leading to serious injury or death.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly and unintentionally

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive oil consumption can lead to premature engine wear, damage to the catalytic converter, and potentially cause engine failure, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Loss of oil (typically 2 quarts or more every 2 weeks)

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Excessive Oil Consumption and Engine Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The excessive oil consumption can lead to engine failure, causing the vehicle to stall or shut off, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded. The engine failure can also cause damage to other components, leading to costly repairs.
symptoms: The vehicle burns oil extremely fast

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Piston Ring Failure and Engine Damage
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the piston rings can cause engine damage, leading to holes in the engine, connecting rod failure, and metal shavings in the engine. This can result in engine failure, stalling, or shutting off, which can cause accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: and metal shavings in the engine.
